you should use &quot;some.package.MyClass.TestMyClass.class&quot;

But I don&#39;t like the mixing of production and test code.
There is no need for static inner class here as far as I can see.
Just make it an &quot;external&quot; class, and if you need to access getter and
setter methods, make them public...


